HEADWORD: Predestinator
<hw>Pre*des"ti*na`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧destinateur</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
predestinates, or foreordains.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who holds to the doctrine of predestination; a
predestinarian.</def> <rj><au>Cowley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predestine</ent>⟦br⟧
